                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/784.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 31. Yesterday the First Chief issued decree reducing taxes to
                    six pesos per pertenencia for the quarter ending November this year; eight pesos
                    for quarter ending February 1916. Commencing March 1916 the rates of the decree
                    of March 1, 1915, will be effective for taxes pending prior to July 31, 1915.
                    Six pesos annual for each pertenencia up to twenty-five pertenencias may be
                    paid, and for each pertenencia exceeding twenty-five three pesos per
                    pertenencia, annual. To those who have already paid the rates established by the
                    decree of March 1, 1915, the excess be returned. Payments may be made up to
                    September 30 without fine. Please advise Consul General, Monterey; full text
                    decree by first mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
